{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Sync Changes to compliance-copilot",
  "description": "After a spec task completes in STIP-KaleAnalyzer or STIP-KaleMCP, automatically port the changes to the generic compliance-copilot project. Strips all Amazon-internal references (Kale, STIP, internal URLs, internal service names) and maps module names accordingly.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "postTaskExecution"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "A spec task just completed. Review the changes made in STIP-KaleAnalyzer and/or STIP-KaleMCP and port them to the compliance-copilot project. Refer to the compliance-copilot-sync steering rules for full sanitization details.\n\n## Module Mapping (STIP-KaleAnalyzer)\n- kale_data_extractor/ → compliance_extractor/\n- kale_reviewer/ → compliance_reviewer/\n- lambdas/ → lambdas/\n- scripts/ → scripts/\n- tests/ → tests/\n- infrastructure/ → infrastructure/\n\n## Module Mapping (STIP-KaleMCP)\n- STIP-KaleMCP/src/STIP-KaleMCP/src/stip_kale_mcp/ → compliance_mcp/\n- STIP-KaleMCP/src/STIP-KaleMCP/src/stip_kale_mcp/tools/ → compliance_mcp/tools/\n- STIP-KaleMCP/src/STIP-KaleMCP/test/ → tests/ (MCP-related tests)\n\n## Sanitization Rules\n1. Replace all references to \"Kale\" with \"Compliance\" (or appropriate generic term)\n2. Replace \"STIP\" with nothing or a generic project name\n3. Remove any Amazon-internal URLs (*.amazon.com, *.amazon.dev, *.a2z.com)\n4. Remove references to internal services (Midway, Bindles, Odin, Apollo, etc.)\n5. Replace internal auth mechanisms with generic placeholders\n6. Remove any internal team names, aliases, or org references\n7. Keep the core logic and patterns intact — only strip identifying details\n8. Update import paths: kale_data_extractor → compliance_extractor, kale_reviewer → compliance_reviewer, stip_kale_mcp → compliance_mcp\n9. MCP tool names: kale_lookup → compliance_lookup, kale_review → compliance_review, kale_findings → compliance_findings, kale_stats → compliance_stats\n\n## Process\n1. Check the git diff in BOTH STIP-KaleAnalyzer and STIP-KaleMCP to see what changed\n2. Identify the corresponding files in compliance-copilot\n3. Apply the equivalent changes with sanitization\n4. If a file doesn't exist yet in compliance-copilot, create it (sanitized)\n5. Run any existing tests in compliance-copilot to verify nothing broke"
  }
}